notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T10:49:22.230Z",unknown,"## PR #15 finishing record (2026-07-10)\n\n**Branch:** feat/agent-enhancement-pass → main. PR was CONFLICTING.\n\n### Merge resolution (faithful)\n- Conflicted files: manifest.json, package.json (only version + description; main bumped to 2026.7.7, PR added agent-workflow = 7th preset).\n- Resolved: kept mainline version 2026.7.7, kept PR feature (agent-workflow, 7 presets). Source files merged cleanly (main only bumped version).\n\n### Bot findings addressed\n1. Greptile P1 / cubic P2(conf9) / gemini — missing empty-name guard on `presets --custom`: added explicit `name.trim().length === 0` guard mirroring `presets export` (defense-in-depth; whitespace is also caught earlier by readStringOption's trim + the requires-a-flag guard, so no invalid preset can ever be produced).\n2. cubic P1(conf10) — version regression 2026.6.10→ fixed by merge (now 2026.7.7).\n3. cubic P2(conf10) + P3(conf10) + Greptile — catalog.summary/tags stale (\"All 5\", 5 tags): synced to 7 presets; tags now include kanban, agent-workflow, agent-setup.\n4. cubic P2(conf6) — **REAL functional bug, verified**: AgentRun custom option key `status` collided with pm's built-in `status` field; templates set `status:\"queued\"` which pm rejects (\"Invalid status value queued. Allowed: draft, open, in_progress, blocked, closed, canceled\"). Renamed the custom option to `agentStatus` (distinct from built-in status; mirrors kanban's non-colliding `column` option). Templates now set `agentStatus`. Verified: `pm create --template agent-task` now succeeds; `--type-option agentStatus=nonsense` gives a clean CommandError with allowed-values hint; valid values accepted.\n5. Greptile nit — test \"non-kanban presets register no custom item types\" name now inaccurate (agent-workflow also registers AgentRun): renamed to \"software-sprint registers no custom item types\".\n\n### Functional verification (throwaway workspace /tmp/fx-pm-presets, pm install local build)\n- Load-time safety: `timeout 20 pm --help` → exit 0 (no fork-bomb/hang).\n- `pm agent-setup` applies preset + writes 3 templates.\n- `pm create --template agent-task|prompt-experiment|eval-run` → all 3 create AgentRun items (was BROKEN before the agentStatus fix).\n- `pm presets --list` → 7 presets; `--diff agent-workflow` → inSync true; `--custom my-config` → exports JSON; `--custom \"   \"` / no flag / too many flags → clean USAGE errors exit 2.\n- Defaults unchanged: diffed `pm presets list` output against origin/main build — existing 6 presets byte-identical; only addition is the agent-workflow row + count 6→7.\n- Existing `presets list/show/export` subcommands unchanged.\n\n### Tests / build / changelog\n- `npm run build` clean; `npm test` → 44/44 pass (0 fail).\n- `npm run changelog:full` + `npm run changelog:check` → pass (\"Changelog is up to date\").\n\n### Not verified\n- Could not run Sourcery/CodeRabbit reviews (rate-limited at review time).\n- Custom type-option values (agentStatus/mode/model) are not auto-applied from templates (only built-in fields are) — this is pm-cli's template behavior, identical for kanban's `column`; custom values set via `--type-option` work correctly. Not a PR defect."
body: ""
